00:21:13,392 --> 00:21:15,006
Anyone there?

270
00:21:15,232 --> 00:21:16,779
Ma'am.

271
00:21:17,532 --> 00:21:18,285
Ma'am.

272
00:21:32,181 --> 00:21:34,068
She sometime is like that.

273
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:36,767
Cerebral anemia?

274
00:21:39,172 --> 00:21:39,879
Do you have any alcohol?

275
00:21:40,287 --> 00:21:41,580
I'll just have a glass of wine.

276
00:21:45,478 --> 00:21:46,938
Call doctor.

277
00:21:47,151 --> 00:21:47,791
OK.

278
00:22:45,395 --> 00:22:46,562
I'm alright.

279
00:22:47,455 --> 00:22:48,442
Sorry.

280
00:22:50,072 --> 00:22:52,232
I'm sorry, I didn't mean to say it.

281
00:22:53,085 --> 00:22:54,018
Don't worry.

282
00:22:58,097 --> 00:22:59,004
Thank you very much.

283
00:23:18,325 --> 00:23:19,059
Koji.

284
00:23:20,175 --> 00:23:20,815
What?

285
00:23:21,775 --> 00:23:24,408
Open the drawer.

286
00:23:31,730 --> 00:23:33,677
You'll find some papers in there.

287
00:23:41,319 --> 00:23:42,099
Read them.

288
00:23:45,321 --> 00:23:48,221
It's all about my husband's women.

289
00:23:49,568 --> 00:23:51,368
About Machiko

290
00:23:53,697 --> 00:23:55,070
Did you ask to do this?

291
00:23:55,672 --> 00:23:56,632
Yes.

292
00:23:59,208 --> 00:24:01,721
I know everything.

293
00:24:04,100 --> 00:24:07,973
But don't ever tell my husband about this.

294
00:24:10,344 --> 00:24:11,918
I'm happy just to know.

295
00:24:14,341 --> 00:24:17,854
It's the only thing that keeps me alive now that he doesn't know.

296
00:24:19,349 --> 00:24:21,362
You must keep it a secret.

297
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:25,487
If you betray me

298
00:24:26,925 --> 00:24:27,991
I'd die.

299
00:24:34,490 --> 00:24:37,677
How often I am frustrated with that person.

300
00:24:38,480 --> 00:24:41,446
What frustrating and strange days they were.

301
00:24:42,932 --> 00:24:45,558
An unhappy, desperate woman and a carefree man

302
00:24:46,171 --> 00:24:48,578
and me, hot-blooded and sympathetic

303
00:24:50,412 --> 00:24:56,965
I guess I didn't realize at the time that the simple scheme hid a terrible trap

304
00:25:00,768 --> 00:25:03,582
Yamada-san, Kinoshita-san, go to the first ward.

305
00:25:04,047 --> 00:25:09,513
The only abnormality I can think of is some low blood pressure, but that's just my nature.

306
00:25:10,312 --> 00:25:14,732
Dizziness like yours has a strong name: dysautonomia.

307
00:25:15,604 --> 00:25:18,437
Are you experiencing any intense anxiety or worry?

308
00:25:18,645 --> 00:25:19,539
No.

309
00:25:21,938 --> 00:25:23,837
It will go away when you get some rest.

310
00:25:24,050 --> 00:25:25,630
It's not a disease.

311
00:25:26,603 --> 00:25:28,483
Your body is in good health.

312
00:26:07,651 --> 00:26:08,764
I'm sorry to have kept you waiting

313
00:26:09,217 --> 00:26:09,937
It must have been hot.

314
00:26:10,468 --> 00:26:13,741
I should have given this to you.
What's this?

315
00:26:15,048 --> 00:26:17,575
I found this.
I'm curious.

316
00:26:17,801 --> 00:26:18,422
Why?

317
00:26:19,008 --> 00:26:21,321
I've been here for two hours now and I didn't even notice.

318
00:26:22,797 --> 00:26:24,004
It's like this fell from the stars.

319
00:26:25,275 --> 00:26:27,028
It doesn't matter.

320
00:26:28,256 --> 00:26:29,449
Throw it away.

321
00:26:31,194 --> 00:26:32,128
How was it?

322
00:26:32,814 --> 00:26:34,254
Doctor said no problem.

323
00:26:36,404 --> 00:26:37,697
I'm old.

324
00:26:37,944 --> 00:26:39,537
You're still young.

325
00:26:40,032 --> 00:26:43,779
But I look at my husband's face, and I think we're both getting older.

326
00:26:43,943 --> 00:26:45,476
Let's not talk about your husband.

327
00:26:46,761 --> 00:26:49,581
It's an uncomfortable subject for me as well.
You're not the only one.

328
00:26:49,929 --> 00:26:51,689
You're not the only one who's unconsciously talking about it?

329
00:26:53,239 --> 00:26:58,433
It's my song.
Can't I sing this song?
It's my song.

330
00:26:59,031 --> 00:27:01,611
You want me to sing in the chorus too?
Do you want me to sing with you?

331
00:27:02,672 --> 00:27:03,359
No way.

332
00:27:04,559 --> 00:27:07,739
It's a cowardly song that's all pride and no courage.

333
00:27:11,793 --> 00:27:14,366
If you fight with your husband, I'll give you any advice you want.

334
00:27:15,749 --> 00:27:18,403
I don't want to hear you complain without a fight.

335
00:27:21,180 --> 00:27:24,499
What are you mad at me for?
What do you want from me?

336
00:27:25,952 --> 00:27:29,452
You're being selfish.
What right do you have to tell me what to do?

337
00:27:31,018 --> 00:27:32,325
What's the hell about it.

338
00:27:33,812 --> 00:27:34,459
Have a seat.

339
00:27:35,650 --> 00:27:37,190
It's too hot.

340
00:27:38,016 --> 00:27:39,096
I'm leaving.

341
00:28:02,266 --> 00:28:02,892
Ma'am.

342
00:28:03,849 --> 00:28:04,996
Shall we visit him tonight?

343
00:28:06,697 --> 00:28:07,424
To where?

344
00:28:08,715 --> 00:28:10,248
Machiko's apartment.

345
00:28:15,278 --> 00:28:17,772
We'll find they are having sex.

346
00:28:18,460 --> 00:28:20,393
It makes you to fight with him.

347
00:28:21,024 --> 00:28:22,010
This is good idea.

348
00:28:22,344 --> 00:28:23,364
No way.

349
00:28:23,723 --> 00:28:24,210
Why not?

350
00:28:24,370 --> 00:28:25,143
Because.

351
00:28:25,891 --> 00:28:29,438
Because if I see it, it's bound to be even worse than what I know from the letters on the paperwork.

352
00:28:30,239 --> 00:28:33,072
You're a coward.

353
00:28:33,473 --> 00:28:36,800
A kid like you wouldn't understand.

354
00:28:38,159 --> 00:28:42,164
You're just too afraid to face reality.

355
00:28:43,256 --> 00:28:46,141
If it makes him upset,It will work.

356
00:28:47,015 --> 00:28:50,542
If I see the look on his face and he doesn't panic, It's all over.

357
00:28:51,268 --> 00:28:52,735
That'd be fine.

358
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:56,514
Why can't I stay like this?

359
00:28:57,943 --> 00:29:01,323
If I go like this, you won't be harmed.

360
00:29:02,214 --> 00:29:05,093
You're lying.
You can't go on like this.

361
00:29:05,884 --> 00:29:07,904
I can't tolerate lies that have nothing to do with me.

362
00:29:09,302 --> 00:29:12,016
Anyway, I can't stand this grotesque reality.

363
00:29:12,449 --> 00:29:14,042
I want to destroy this grotesque world.

364
00:29:14,901 --> 00:29:18,841
Do you hate him or me?

365
00:29:19,232 --> 00:29:20,012
Both.

366
00:29:23,957 --> 00:29:25,184
It's Tuesday, isn't it?

367
00:29:27,024 --> 00:29:29,017
I'm sure he is visiting that woman.

368
00:30:47,465 --> 00:30:48,698
Why you are here?

369
00:31:22,275 --> 00:31:25,149
Koji.
You are here too.

370
00:31:26,146 --> 00:31:28,159
How did you find here?

371
00:31:29,569 --> 00:31:32,115
I'm sure she appreciates you.

372
00:31:36,149 --> 00:31:40,263
Just shut up and go home.

373
00:31:42,552 --> 00:31:46,246
I think it's counterproductive to ask me to leave with that kind of attitude.

374
00:31:47,518 --> 00:31:49,565
That's not so you.

375
00:31:51,875 --> 00:31:54,588
I wouldn't be able to go home either.

376
00:31:55,680 --> 00:31:58,734
It's a bad idea to bring things to a close at the last minute.

377
00:31:59,653 --> 00:32:02,073
We have to be concerned about her position.

378
00:32:03,627 --> 00:32:05,367
Go home with Koji first.

379
00:32:14,970 --> 00:32:16,390
You're so terrible.

380
00:32:17,627 --> 00:32:21,534
I have been holding back.

381
00:32:22,335 --> 00:32:24,182
I love you so much.

382
00:32:26,370 --> 00:32:29,783
I believed in you.

383
00:32:32,414 --> 00:32:33,721
You're so terrible.

384
00:32:37,134 --> 00:32:41,654
I've waited so long for your heart to come back to me

385
00:32:43,521 --> 00:32:45,475
I love you so much.

386
00:32:47,068 --> 00:32:48,468
You're so terrible.

387
00:32:53,011 --> 00:32:55,538
Please leave now.

388
00:33:00,914 --> 00:33:03,027
Go home with me.

389
00:34:06,670 --> 00:34:13,700
The saint said that man was born to suffer in this world

390
00:34:15,015 --> 00:34:20,755
He also said that man cannot live without making mistakes.

391
00:34:21,913 --> 00:34:25,907
By mistakes, he did not mean that we make mistakes.

392
00:34:27,282 --> 00:34:34,196
It means to hate others, to envy others, to bully others, to fight others.

393
00:34:34,747 --> 00:34:38,434
We all have greed.

394
00:34:39,117 --> 00:34:43,137
This greed is always centered on oneself.

395
00:34:44,331 --> 00:34:51,424
Because you try to push your own greed, you will never find peace of mind.

396
00:34:56,032 --> 00:34:58,852
Your underwriter's name is listed as Yuko Kusakado.

397
00:34:59,547 --> 00:35:02,380
This is the wife of the victim of your disability, is it not?

398
00:35:02,945 --> 00:35:03,398
Yes.

399
00:35:04,026 --> 00:35:05,566
I've never heard of anything like this.

400
00:35:06,613 --> 00:35:11,133
The lady's letter says she wants to take you back because you committed the crime for her own good.

401
00:35:12,194 --> 00:35:13,827
I guess it's called humanitarianism.

402
00:35:14,685 --> 00:35:15,998
The money has arrived.

403
00:35:16,447 --> 00:35:17,420
Give me the note.

404
00:35:19,781 --> 00:35:22,047
You will be taken in by the victim.

405
00:35:23,513 --> 00:35:26,440
You will never make a mistake again against the victim.

406
00:35:27,814 --> 00:35:31,947
If you're even a little nervous yourself, I'd be happy to consider changing underwriters.

407
00:35:34,240 --> 00:35:34,946
Don't worry.

408
00:35:35,885 --> 00:35:38,152
From now on, you will live a life of gratitude.

409
00:35:39,453 --> 00:35:42,120
When the going gets tough, remember your life here and persevere.

410
00:35:42,970 --> 00:35:45,603
You are never to come back here again.

411
00:35:47,983 --> 00:35:48,416
You swear?

412
00:35:49,170 --> 00:35:49,683
I swear.

413
00:37:04,261 --> 00:37:04,947
Please.

414
00:37:13,082 --> 00:37:14,042
Welcome back.

415
00:37:15,077 --> 00:37:16,350
Thank you for everything you've done for me.

416
00:37:17,396 --> 00:37:18,989
I've been waiting a long time for you.

417
00:37:20,379 --> 00:37:21,639
You look so nice.

418
00:37:22,174 --> 00:37:23,588
Thank you.

419
00:37:24,074 --> 00:37:25,267
I'm glad to see you're doing so well.

420
00:37:26,298 --> 00:37:28,384
You're looking better than ever.

421
00:37:29,206 --> 00:37:30,052
A villa?

422
00:37:30,946 --> 00:37:32,672
It's halfway up that mountainside.

423
00:37:33,640 --> 00:37:35,320
I'd like to have a few words with you before we go.

424
00:37:35,893 --> 00:37:39,267
I know you do.
That's what I thought, so I brought you this.

425
00:37:40,539 --> 00:37:43,205
It's a village without a single coffee shop.

426
00:38:05,022 --> 00:38:06,382
You don't care about your house?

427
00:38:06,990 --> 00:38:08,563
About him?

428
00:38:09,482 --> 00:38:11,589
He's at home today. He's eating lunch alone.

429
00:38:12,349 --> 00:38:13,498
That's better than meeting him out of the blue.

430
00:38:15,302 --> 00:38:17,529
Of course, he's very eager for you to come.

431
00:38:19,209 --> 00:38:21,677
He's made himself at home like the Buddha.

432
00:38:25,130 --> 00:38:26,482
There are no mirrors in prison.

433
00:38:27,365 --> 00:38:33,193
Of course I don't need one.
But when I'm getting close to getting out, suddenly I start to worry about my face.

434
00:38:34,763 --> 00:38:42,677
I worry about how I look to humans.
So, as an inmate nears release, he wants not only his number, but his face.

435
00:38:44,138 --> 00:38:48,326
I had no choice but to put a dustpan outside the windowpane and use it as a mirror.

436
00:38:50,787 --> 00:38:53,630
Look.
You've never changed.

437
00:38:54,420 --> 00:38:56,068
There's not a shadow anywhere.

438
00:38:59,987 --> 00:39:02,198
You haven't changed at all.

439
00:39:04,643 --> 00:39:06,838
I'm sorry I never got to visit you.

440
00:39:07,721 --> 00:39:10,612
And the reason I gave in my letter, it's because it's true.

441
00:39:11,604 --> 00:39:15,705
He's too sick to be away from home overnight.

442
00:39:16,721 --> 00:39:21,159
As you can see, he's in a state of flux without me.

443
00:39:21,854 --> 00:39:23,198
I'm sure you are satisfied.

444
00:39:25,235 --> 00:39:26,462
What do you mean by that?

445
00:39:27,173 --> 00:39:29,743
I mean that he's not going to run away from me again.

446
00:39:31,970 --> 00:39:34,806
That's the first thing you were going to say when you came out.

447
00:39:36,079 --> 00:39:38,915
Oh, my God, that's such a horrible thing to say.

448
00:39:40,384 --> 00:39:42,704
If you said that, everything would be so screwed up.

449
00:39:46,337 --> 00:39:49,642
Promise me you won't say that, please.

450
00:39:51,339 --> 00:39:52,675
I didn't mean it like that.

451
00:40:05,441 --> 00:40:06,863
They're talking about us.

452
00:40:07,230 --> 00:40:08,949
I wonder how long we'll be rare.

453
00:40:16,861 --> 00:40:19,275
It's hot day,isn't?

454
00:40:32,097 --> 00:40:34,511
You shouldn't walk around with your eyes down so low.

455
00:40:51,915 --> 00:40:52,907
Going out?

456
00:40:53,001 --> 00:40:56,634
I'm just visiting my parishioners.
You always bring flowers, don't you?

457
00:40:57,337 --> 00:40:58,884
He is.

458
00:41:00,805 --> 00:41:01,813
Welcome back.

459
00:41:02,657 --> 00:41:05,587
I'm glad to see you're doing well.

460
00:41:07,821 --> 00:41:10,595
Come visit me when you get settled.

461
00:41:14,634 --> 00:41:17,657
I've told that monk about you and everything.

462
00:41:18,180 --> 00:41:21,376
He's a very nice man.
He's my confidant.

463
00:41:22,126 --> 00:41:24,665
He immediately agreed to invite you.

464
00:41:25,251 --> 00:41:26,516
I don't like the monk much.

465
00:41:27,266 --> 00:41:29,899
The churchwarden at the prison was a monk.
I didn't like him

466
00:41:30,470 --> 00:41:31,962
Don't talk to me about prison.

467
00:41:44,184 --> 00:41:47,207
Here... here...
There he is.

468
00:41:55,947 --> 00:41:58,564
He's messy.

469
00:42:10,929 --> 00:42:13,101
Clean your face.

470
00:42:14,047 --> 00:42:16,640
He's Koji.

471
00:42:22,933 --> 00:42:25,261
Not Kori but Koji.

472
00:42:25,714 --> 00:42:27,175
Don't you remember him?

473
00:42:28,722 --> 00:42:30,487
Koji.

474
00:42:31,519 --> 00:42:32,292
Hello.

475
00:42:32,901 --> 00:42:36,206
That's strange.
He's been able to say it smoothly from the beginning.

476
00:42:39,011 --> 00:42:40,808
I'll show you around.

477
00:42:47,730 --> 00:42:50,214
Now this greenhouse is where we do our business.

478
00:42:50,573 --> 00:42:53,855
Tokyo Gardening is doing business with us out of kindness for old time's sake.

479
00:42:54,347 --> 00:42:57,691
Actually, we'd like you to help us with this job.

480
00:42:59,878 --> 00:43:01,823
That man is our helper SADA.

481
00:43:04,698 --> 00:43:06,847
It's not that the work is difficult.

482
00:43:07,175 --> 00:43:12,894
It's just the temperature control that's a little tricky.
But I think you're going to love it.

483
00:43:22,710 --> 00:43:24,624
There are still a few.

484
00:43:27,796 --> 00:43:28,585
These flowers.

485
00:43:29,789 --> 00:43:31,242
Cymbidiums?

486
00:43:32,523 --> 00:43:34,835
You gave it to me when I first came to see you.

487
00:43:35,226 --> 00:43:37,453
I'm surprised you remember it.

488
00:43:42,023 --> 00:43:43,601
Koji.

489
00:43:55,810 --> 00:43:58,630
I wonder if you drink water with relish.

490
00:43:59,880 --> 00:44:01,372
Wanna drink?

491
00:44:31,305 --> 00:44:32,672
okay?

492
00:44:36,711 --> 00:44:38,242
Come on, let's go.

493
00:44:50,038 --> 00:44:51,913
I'll show you your room.

494
00:44:52,444 --> 00:44:54,006
Your room is on the second floor.

495
00:44:54,225 --> 00:44:57,936
It's very well-ventilated, so you'll find it cooler than downstairs.
Please come.

496
00:45:05,187 --> 00:45:08,163
The wind from the ocean comes through best in this room.

497
00:45:11,929 --> 00:45:14,929
I was going to get down on my knees and apologize to him, but I couldn't.

498
00:45:16,687 --> 00:45:18,366
I really feel sorry for him.

499
00:45:20,851 --> 00:45:23,304
It's over.

500
00:45:23,780 --> 00:45:24,687
No, it's not.

501
00:45:24,937 --> 00:45:28,358
You've been paying for your sins for three years.

502
00:45:28,491 --> 00:45:29,663
That's another issue.

503
00:45:30,616 --> 00:45:33,327
Just because I've been socially punished doesn't mean I can apologize to him.

504
00:45:34,022 --> 00:45:37,210
He is the one who should apologize to you.

505
00:45:37,319 --> 00:45:38,390
No way.

506
00:45:40,966 --> 00:45:45,911
I must confess, I didn't think he was terribly different.

507
00:45:47,833 --> 00:45:51,997
So the moment I saw him, I suddenly got choked up, and I forgot to say I was sorry.

508
00:45:52,552 --> 00:45:53,989
It's called aphasia.

509
00:45:54,763 --> 00:45:58,185
He understands a lot of what we say.
He just can't speak.

510
00:45:58,802 --> 00:46:01,302
He's forgotten most of the words he speaks.

511
00:46:01,630 --> 00:46:06,145
So it's normal for him to be frustrated, but he's so laid back.

512
00:46:06,520 --> 00:46:08,239
Maybe he's more serious than that.

513
00:46:08,786 --> 00:46:10,364
But it's easy to communicate.

514
00:46:14,622 --> 00:46:15,677
Yuko.

515
00:46:31,584 --> 00:46:32,717
What kind of variety is this?

516
00:46:33,115 --> 00:46:35,420
It sells well as the Kannon flower.

517
00:46:36,318 --> 00:46:37,600
You been in this business long?

518
00:46:37,904 --> 00:46:41,810
This wife taught me everything.
I used to be a fisherman.

519
00:46:42,912 --> 00:46:43,545
You have wife?

520
00:46:43,904 --> 00:46:46,084
She ran away while I was in the army.

521
00:46:46,709 --> 00:46:51,381
Even if you're like your husband here, you still have someone wonderful like his wife.

522
00:46:53,443 --> 00:46:54,178
Kids?

523
00:46:54,475 --> 00:46:57,560
One daughter works at a music factory in Hamamatsu.

524
00:46:58,053 --> 00:46:59,904
She's a troubled girl

525
00:47:01,029 --> 00:47:01,529
What?

526
00:47:01,865 --> 00:47:04,982
Like her mother, she's play girl.

527
00:47:10,820 --> 00:47:13,750
Hey, your tea is ready.

528
00:47:14,578 --> 00:47:16,414
Come on.

529
00:47:24,719 --> 00:47:26,383
You getting used to the job?

530
00:47:26,641 --> 00:47:27,563
